Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.90,0:00:04.53,Default,,0,0,0,,This convention program will be translated
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.53,0:00:07.58,Default,,0,0,0,,into more than 400 languages.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.57,0:00:12.07,Default,,0,0,0,,This work is supported\Nby branch offices around the globe.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.07,0:00:15.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Each of us has an opportunity\Nto show appreciation
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.95,0:00:20.66,Default,,0,0,0,,for the spiritual blessings\Nwe have received in our own language.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.67,0:00:24.92,Default,,0,0,0,,One way we can do this\Nis by making voluntary gifts
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.92,0:00:27.80,Default,,0,0,0,,in accord with our circumstances.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.80,0:00:30.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Donations can be made online
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.13,0:00:35.01,Default,,0,0,0,,at donate.jw.org.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.94,0:00:40.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Please be seated.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.73,0:00:45.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you faced serious obstacles
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.11,0:00:47.95,Default,,0,0,0,,as you try to do what Jehovah commands?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.94,0:00:50.07,Default,,0,0,0,,How can servants of God
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.07,0:00:54.37,Default,,0,0,0,,maintain their joy despite such challenges?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.37,0:00:58.62,Default,,0,0,0,,We invite you to watch and learn\Nfrom the drama
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.62,0:01:04.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}Nehemiah: “The Joy of Jehovah{\r}\N{\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}Is Your Stronghold”—Part I.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.97,0:01:14.56,Default,,0,0,0,,As we learned in our audio drama,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.55,0:01:16.64,Default,,0,0,0,,the Jews returned to Jerusalem
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.64,0:01:21.02,Default,,0,0,0,,to rebuild the temple in 537 B.C.E.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.02,0:01:26.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And by 515 B.C.E., it was finally completed.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.02,0:01:30.61,Default,,0,0,0,,However, the city’s walls were still left in ruins.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.61,0:01:34.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah’s time had now come to rebuild the walls,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.57,0:01:37.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and he used the faithful man Nehemiah
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.41,0:01:39.83,Default,,0,0,0,,to take the lead in this work.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.83,0:01:43.38,Default,,0,0,0,,This would be a massive undertaking for the Jews.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.38,0:01:46.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And once again, there were opposers.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.34,0:01:48.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Nehemiah told the nation of Israel
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.92,0:01:52.38,Default,,0,0,0,,that “the joy of Jehovah is your stronghold.”
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.38,0:01:56.05,Default,,0,0,0,,How could he encourage them to be joyful
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.05,0:01:58.64,Default,,0,0,0,,despite all the opposition?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.64,0:02:02.35,Default,,0,0,0,,What lessons can we learn from their example?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.35,0:02:04.35,Default,,0,0,0,,There are many,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.35,0:02:07.35,Default,,0,0,0,,but here are three to think about as you watch:
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.86,0:02:12.32,Default,,0,0,0,,What role did prayer play in helping Nehemiah
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.32,0:02:15.95,Default,,0,0,0,,to be a courageous person for Jehovah?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.95,0:02:18.75,Default,,0,0,0,,In addition to direct attacks,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.74,0:02:21.91,Default,,0,0,0,,what schemes did the enemies employ
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.91,0:02:24.33,Default,,0,0,0,,to oppose the work?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.33,0:02:25.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Despite setbacks,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.96,0:02:30.09,Default,,0,0,0,,what was Nehemiah’s main source of joy?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.46,0:02:31.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Got it?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.67,0:02:35.63,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, then, with that in mind, please sit back
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.64,0:02:39.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and enjoy the following video presentation
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.06,0:02:43.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}“The Joy of Jehovah Is Your Stronghold.”
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.74,0:02:53.74,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a privilege to have a share
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.74,0:02:56.45,Default,,0,0,0,,in the restoration of Jehovah’s worship.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.24,0:03:00.49,Default,,0,0,0,,People know we rebuilt the wall,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.08,0:03:06.46,Default,,0,0,0,,but there is so much more to the story.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.46,0:03:09.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s start at the beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.46,0:03:17.13,Default,,0,0,0,,In the 20th year of King Artaxerxes Longimanus,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.14,0:03:20.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I was in Shushan the palace.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.64,0:03:23.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I was cupbearer to the king.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.28,0:03:37.24,Default,,0,0,0,,He trusted me with his life.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.53,0:03:41.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Although I was far from Jerusalem,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.79,0:03:44.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I found great joy just thinking
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.04,0:03:47.09,Default,,0,0,0,,about our people there serving Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.46,0:03:50.92,Default,,0,0,0,,—until one day when I received a visit
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.92,0:03:52.92,Default,,0,0,0,,from my brother Hanani.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.92,0:03:55.34,Default,,0,0,0,,That visit changed everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.52,0:04:07.52,Default,,0,0,0,,What’s going on, Hanani?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.56,0:04:11.10,Default,,0,0,0,,How are our people?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.11,0:04:12.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Not good.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.44,0:04:16.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The conditions are disgraceful.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.28,0:04:19.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The walls of Jerusalem are broken down,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.82,0:04:22.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and its gates have been burned with fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.37,0:04:25.79,Default,,0,0,0,,What about the temple?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.79,0:04:26.79,Default,,0,0,0,,It stands,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.79,0:04:29.67,Default,,0,0,0,,but the services are nothing but empty rituals.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.54,0:04:34.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Most of the people and the priests ignore God’s Law.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.38,0:04:37.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to return with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.89,0:04:50.64,Default,,0,0,0,,For days, my conscience plagued me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.07,0:04:58.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Would the king even allow me to go?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.45,0:05:05.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Our people had sinned
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.45,0:05:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,by not keeping Jehovah’s commandments,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.00,0:05:13.25,Default,,0,0,0,,but now I felt as if I were sinning
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.25,0:05:16.30,Default,,0,0,0,,by not helping them in their time of need.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.30,0:05:20.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I begged Jehovah to grant me success.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.10,0:05:31.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Nehemiah,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.81,0:05:34.77,Default,,0,0,0,,why are you so gloomy when you’re not sick?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.78,0:05:37.24,Default,,0,0,0,,This can be nothing but gloominess of heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.32,0:05:41.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Why should I not look gloomy
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.78,0:05:43.82,Default,,0,0,0,,when the city,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.83,0:05:45.54,Default,,0,0,0,,the place where my forefathers are buried,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.54,0:05:46.92,Default,,0,0,0,,lies in ruins,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.91,0:05:49.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and its gates have been consumed by fire?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.04,0:05:51.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Nehemiah, what is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.38,0:05:52.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Speak frankly.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.42,0:05:53.67,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you seeking?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.75,0:05:59.59,Default,,0,0,0,,At once, I prayed to the God of the heavens.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.51,0:06:05.80,Default,,0,0,0,,If it pleases the king
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.81,0:06:10.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and if your servant has found favor with you,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.60,0:06:12.60,Default,,0,0,0,,send me to Judah,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.60,0:06:14.85,Default,,0,0,0,,to the city where my forefathers are buried,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.86,0:06:16.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and let me rebuild it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.20,0:06:24.37,Default,,0,0,0,,You may go.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.49,0:06:28.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah was with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.21,0:06:33.63,Default,,0,0,0,,The king gave me supplies,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.63,0:06:35.76,Default,,0,0,0,,an army,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.75,0:06:38.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and an appointment as governor.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.01,0:06:45.93,Default,,0,0,0,,We were on our way to help rebuild Jerusalem’s walls.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.73,0:07:36.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I had seen a portion of the city,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.02,0:07:38.02,Default,,0,0,0,,but it wasn’t until I rose
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.02,0:07:40.86,Default,,0,0,0,,by night to inspect the walls
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.86,0:07:44.32,Default,,0,0,0,,that I saw just how badly God’s city had been treated.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.58,0:07:55.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.81,0:08:19.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn’t believe the destruction.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.33,0:08:29.87,Default,,0,0,0,,The time had come
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.87,0:08:32.25,Default,,0,0,0,,to reveal Jehovah’s purpose for Jerusalem.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.04,0:08:35.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I gathered the leaders.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.33,0:08:39.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Who is this man?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.29,0:08:43.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m told he’s Nehemiah, cupbearer to the king.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.17,0:08:46.30,Default,,0,0,0,,What does he want from us?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.01,0:08:49.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Men!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.85,0:08:58.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The holy city is completely vulnerable.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.61,0:09:02.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Let us rebuild the walls of Jerusalem,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.19,0:09:04.53,Default,,0,0,0,,so that this disgrace will not continue.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.53,0:09:06.24,Default,,0,0,0,,But what will our neighbors think?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.24,0:09:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, we have many powerful enemies.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.70,0:09:11.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Artaxerxes commissioned me
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.70,0:09:14.04,Default,,0,0,0,,to rebuild the walls and the entire city.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.04,0:09:16.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Didn’t you see the horsemen he sent
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.29,0:09:18.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and all the timber?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.42,0:09:20.55,Default,,0,0,0,,He gave it all!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.54,0:09:23.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Brothers, the good hand of our God was upon me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.76,0:09:26.97,Default,,0,0,0,,He is the one to fear, not men.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.97,0:09:29.31,Default,,0,0,0,,He will give us success.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.48,0:09:38.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Not everyone was happy
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.69,0:09:40.78,Default,,0,0,0,,that we had come to do something good
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.77,0:09:42.81,Default,,0,0,0,,for the people of Israel.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.94,0:09:46.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So that’s what this Nehemiah is up to.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.11,0:09:49.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Geshem, do you see what I’m seeing?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.37,0:09:51.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Without a wall,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.62,0:09:53.96,Default,,0,0,0,,we can keep the Jews under control.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.95,0:09:55.95,Default,,0,0,0,,If they rebuild it,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.96,0:09:58.67,Default,,0,0,0,,the Jews won’t need our land or resources.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.67,0:10:00.21,Default,,0,0,0,,That means he’s planning to rebel.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.21,0:10:01.21,Default,,0,0,0,,We can’t let him.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.92,0:10:05.76,Default,,0,0,0,,We must act, and act together.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.76,0:10:06.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.76,0:10:08.01,Default,,0,0,0,,You have my support.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.89,0:10:12.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And mine, as always.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.85,0:10:13.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Good!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.85,0:10:17.15,Default,,0,0,0,,We must go to Jerusalem to keep an eye on Nehemiah.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.23,0:10:22.57,Default,,0,0,0,,The opposers wanted to maintain control
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.57,0:10:24.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and to profit from Jehovah’s people.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.86,0:10:29.03,Default,,0,0,0,,They wasted little time trying to intimidate us.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.45,0:10:35.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Who are these?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.70,0:10:39.33,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s Sanballat, governor of Samaria.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.79,0:10:43.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Next to him is Tobiah, an Ammonite official
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.75,0:10:45.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and landowner to many of our people.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.88,0:10:47.22,Default,,0,0,0,,They all look up to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.22,0:10:49.06,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s Geshem;
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.05,0:10:52.51,Default,,0,0,0,,he’s a very wealthy Arabian and close ally to Sanballat.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.86,0:11:10.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Nehemiah, are you rebelling against the king?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.57,0:11:13.66,Default,,0,0,0,,The king himself gave us the authority.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.66,0:11:15.66,Default,,0,0,0,,To rebuild the city and the wall?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.66,0:11:17.04,Default,,0,0,0,,To rebuild the city and the wall
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.04,0:11:18.92,Default,,0,0,0,,is what the king expects us to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.91,0:11:20.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Why did you not consult with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.92,0:11:23.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I am the governor of Samaria.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.08,0:11:24.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, yes, but the king appointed
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.79,0:11:27.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Nehemiah as governor of Judah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.05,0:11:28.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So why have you not asked for our help?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.72,0:11:30.51,Default,,0,0,0,,We worship Jehovah too.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.51,0:11:32.51,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ve sacrificed to him for generations.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.51,0:11:35.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Along with sacrifices to all of your other gods.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.01,0:11:38.01,Default,,0,0,0,,The God of the heavens
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.02,0:11:40.23,Default,,0,0,0,,is the One that will grant us success,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.23,0:11:42.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and we, his servants,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.15,0:11:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,will get up and build.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.44,0:11:46.36,Default,,0,0,0,,No one should let his religious beliefs
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.36,0:11:48.90,Default,,0,0,0,,come before national unity.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.90,0:11:51.49,Default,,0,0,0,,You have neither share
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.49,0:11:54.49,Default,,0,0,0,,nor claim nor memorial in Jerusalem.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.67,0:12:04.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Sanballat,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.25,0:12:06.25,Default,,0,0,0,,could it be you
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.25,0:12:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,who is rebelling against the highest King of all?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.55,0:12:17.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Despite opposition,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.60,0:12:19.60,Default,,0,0,0,,the people worked strenuously.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.60,0:12:22.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Nehemiah, these things have to go somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.66,0:12:43.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Their struggles went far beyond building a wall.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.17,0:12:46.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah remembers brothers like Peleth.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.84,0:12:50.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Seeing how he dealt with personal challenges
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.21,0:12:52.30,Default,,0,0,0,,strengthened my faith.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.68,0:12:57.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Peleth.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.35,0:12:58.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Raham.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.81,0:13:00.69,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ll never finish this work.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.68,0:13:02.77,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s nothing but rubble.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.77,0:13:04.56,Default,,0,0,0,,At least we’re trying to make a change.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.65,0:13:07.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Always an optimist.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.82,0:13:10.32,Default,,0,0,0,,By the way, you’re late on your rent
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.32,0:13:12.61,Default,,0,0,0,,—again.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.61,0:13:14.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Raham, I’m sorry;
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.61,0:13:16.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I need more time.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.53,0:13:17.99,Default,,0,0,0,,With the work on the wall, . . .
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.99,0:13:19.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I have enough troubles.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.70,0:13:21.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Look, if I don’t get payment
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.41,0:13:22.54,Default,,0,0,0,,by the end of the month,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.54,0:13:24.54,Default,,0,0,0,,you and your family are out.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.96,0:13:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Is there anything we can do?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.55,0:13:33.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe I can work it off till we get caught up.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.88,0:13:34.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Seriously?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.88,0:13:36.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You don’t have time to work it off,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.14,0:13:41.06,Default,,0,0,0,,but maybe your daughter can help.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.06,0:13:43.15,Default,,0,0,0,,She can come stay with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.02,0:13:45.23,Default,,0,0,0,,As a slave?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.23,0:13:47.40,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I’ll hire her to help Azubah
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.40,0:13:49.49,Default,,0,0,0,,—to pay off your debt.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.40,0:13:52.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Look, I’m trying to help,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.03,0:13:54.57,Default,,0,0,0,,but you don’t have many options here, my friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.57,0:13:56.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Think about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.35,0:14:27.27,Default,,0,0,0,,So Raham spoke to me today.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.27,0:14:28.69,Default,,0,0,0,,About what?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.65,0:14:31.74,Default,,0,0,0,,He wants to hire Simcha to help Azubah in the house.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.78,0:14:35.74,Default,,0,0,0,,He says he’ll care for her like his own daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.03,0:14:39.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Imma, I’ve known Raham and Azubah
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.82,0:14:42.37,Default,,0,0,0,,ever since I came here with Ezra.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.37,0:14:43.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Raham helped us.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.83,0:14:46.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Our house belongs to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.00,0:14:48.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I don’t trust him.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.88,0:14:51.47,Default,,0,0,0,,He wants our Simcha to live with him?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.46,0:14:52.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Imma, . . .
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.63,0:14:54.09,Default,,0,0,0,,What about Jehovah’s command
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.09,0:14:56.68,Default,,0,0,0,,that parents raise their own children?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.68,0:14:59.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Don’t you want her to have a better life?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.31,0:15:06.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I-I cannot agree
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.77,0:15:09.40,Default,,0,0,0,,to having her live apart from us,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.40,0:15:11.78,Default,,0,0,0,,even if we have to survive on gleanings.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.77,0:15:13.77,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you know we’ll survive at all?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.07,0:15:17.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Because Jehovah always takes care
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.07,0:15:18.32,Default,,0,0,0,,of those who love and obey him.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.33,0:15:26.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Men like Peleth threw their burden on Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.12,0:15:27.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and kept working.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.72,0:15:41.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Sanballat set up camp near Jerusalem
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.72,0:15:44.68,Default,,0,0,0,,to keep an eye on our progress.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.90,0:15:53.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.44,0:15:54.61,Default,,0,0,0,,My lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.61,0:15:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.36,0:15:56.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The wall
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.03,0:15:58.20,Default,,0,0,0,,—it’s up to half its height all around the city.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.20,0:16:00.04,Default,,0,0,0,,This has gone too far!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.78,0:16:03.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Geshem, how long will it take
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.45,0:16:04.66,Default,,0,0,0,,to assemble an attack force?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.95,0:16:07.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Attack force?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.91,0:16:11.33,Default,,0,0,0,,My lord, Sanballat, an attack on the Jews
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.33,0:16:13.25,Default,,0,0,0,,would be an attack on the king.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.25,0:16:14.50,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.50,0:16:15.71,Default,,0,0,0,,He’s right.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.71,0:16:18.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Nehemiah has authorization from Artaxerxes himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.42,0:16:20.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You saw how many horsemen the king sent with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.26,0:16:20.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.84,0:16:22.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you be talking like this if those horsemen
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.43,0:16:23.47,Default,,0,0,0,,were still here?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.47,0:16:24.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And they can come back.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.39,0:16:25.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Nonsense!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.64,0:16:27.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Never mind the horsemen.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.89,0:16:30.31,Default,,0,0,0,,This is my province!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.31,0:16:33.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Out here, I decide what to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.98,0:16:36.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, we need to threaten them.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.53,0:16:39.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Geshem, you bring Samaritan troops
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.40,0:16:41.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and come in from this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.32,0:16:42.99,Default,,0,0,0,,They’re preparing to attack us!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.99,0:16:43.99,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you know that?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.99,0:16:45.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard them talking.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.66,0:16:49.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Brothers, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.04,0:16:51.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Have they attacked anyone yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.08,0:16:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,They must have.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.00,0:16:52.96,Default,,0,0,0,,He saw something.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.96,0:16:56.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you going to wait until they start killing us?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.17,0:16:57.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course not!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.17,0:16:58.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course not!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.14,0:17:05.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Hanani,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.35,0:17:08.85,Default,,0,0,0,,post men by families at the lowest parts of the wall 
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.85,0:17:10.52,Default,,0,0,0,,—at all the exposed places.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.52,0:17:11.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, Nehemiah.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.56,0:17:12.89,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s not going to work.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.90,0:17:15.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Brothers,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.02,0:17:17.40,Default,,0,0,0,,if we let mere threats frighten us into stopping,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.40,0:17:18.78,Default,,0,0,0,,they will have achieved their goal.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.78,0:17:20.62,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s no use. Don’t you see?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.61,0:17:21.82,Default,,0,0,0,,These people hate what we’re doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.82,0:17:22.82,Default,,0,0,0,,They hate us.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.82,0:17:24.91,Default,,0,0,0,,You don’t have to live and work around them like we do.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.91,0:17:26.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Brothers,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.28,0:17:29.03,Default,,0,0,0,,where is your faith?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.04,0:17:31.17,Default,,0,0,0,,It is Jehovah’s will that we build this wall.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.16,0:17:32.12,Default,,0,0,0,,If it is really Jehovah’s will,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.12,0:17:34.29,Default,,0,0,0,,then why are we getting all this opposition?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.13,0:17:37.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe this isn’t the right time.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.13,0:17:38.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides, this work is too much for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.96,0:17:39.84,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re worn out.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.84,0:17:41.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do we need a wall anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.60,0:17:49.19,Default,,0,0,0,,To protect Jehovah’s people.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.56,0:17:51.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Brothers,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.40,0:17:56.49,Default,,0,0,0,,do not be afraid of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.69,0:17:59.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.73,0:18:03.11,Default,,0,0,0,,who is great and awe-inspiring;
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.11,0:18:05.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and fight for your brothers,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.08,0:18:09.08,Default,,0,0,0,,your sons and daughters,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.62,0:18:13.91,Default,,0,0,0,,your wives and homes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.42,0:18:19.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So when you hear the sound of the horn,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.84,0:18:22.93,Default,,0,0,0,,gather together to where we are.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.92,0:18:26.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Our God will fight for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.31,0:18:30.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen for this signal.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.15,0:18:40.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The threats aren’t working.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.86,0:18:44.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The next sound they hear will be our battle cry.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.28,0:18:44.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.99,0:18:46.49,Default,,0,0,0,,We already spoke about this.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.49,0:18:49.79,Default,,0,0,0,,A direct attack would be seditious.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.79,0:18:52.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides, they’ve armed themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.71,0:18:58.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.29,0:19:00.25,Default,,0,0,0,,My-my lord,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.25,0:19:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Geshem is right.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.01,0:19:05.05,Default,,0,0,0,,We’d never get away with this.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.05,0:19:07.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Don’t you recall who commissioned Nehemiah?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.47,0:19:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It was the king.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.55,0:19:10.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It was the king of Persia, let me remind you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.14,0:19:15.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Nehemiah is setting himself up as a king.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.82,0:19:23.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I recommend we turn the accusation of sedition
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.57,0:19:26.86,Default,,0,0,0,,against Nehemiah.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.86,0:19:28.86,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s brilliant!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.87,0:19:31.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.12,0:19:33.58,Default,,0,0,0,,he will beg for our help.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.58,0:19:35.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s go back to Samaria.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.11,0:20:06.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Hanani,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.29,0:20:15.67,Default,,0,0,0,,you look like you’ve been working.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.71,0:20:18.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I must smell like it too.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.71,0:20:20.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.25,0:20:22.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, you do.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.92,0:20:25.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Brothers!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.22,0:20:30.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Brothers, we are well on our way to completing the wall.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.43,0:20:33.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah is helping us,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.43,0:20:36.22,Default,,0,0,0,,but we must not let our hands drop.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.65,0:20:40.36,Default,,0,0,0,,From now on,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.36,0:20:42.53,Default,,0,0,0,,we will all spend the night inside Jerusalem.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.52,0:20:44.86,Default,,0,0,0,,We will take turns keeping watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.86,0:20:48.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Hanani will give out assignments.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.03,0:20:50.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Good work today.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.45,0:21:30.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone was working hard on the wall.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.33,0:21:37.37,Default,,0,0,0,,But there were more issues to contend with.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.25,0:21:44.84,Default,,0,0,0,,My brothers, how can I help you?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.84,0:21:49.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Nehemiah, we, with our sons and daughters, are many.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.30,0:21:51.51,Default,,0,0,0,,We need food to stay alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.01,0:21:56.39,Default,,0,0,0,,We gave our fields and vineyards
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.39,0:21:59.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and houses as security to get grain during
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.06,0:22:00.48,Default,,0,0,0,,the food shortage.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.48,0:22:02.15,Default,,0,0,0,,We borrowed money
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.15,0:22:04.86,Default,,0,0,0,,on our fields and our vineyards to pay the king’s tribute.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.78,0:22:09.45,Default,,0,0,0,,And we’ve had to sell some of our children into slavery.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.44,0:22:11.69,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re powerless to stop this
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.70,0:22:14.54,Default,,0,0,0,,because our fields and vineyards belong to others.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.16,0:22:19.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for bringing this to my attention.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.58,0:22:21.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I must ponder all this.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.25,0:22:22.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Nehemiah.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.04,0:22:22.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.38,0:22:30.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Hanani, please tell all the nobles
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.67,0:22:32.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and deputy rulers to come to me
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.72,0:22:34.72,Default,,0,0,0,,first thing tomorrow morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.72,0:22:38.27,Default,,0,0,0,,With God’s help, we can make this right.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.45,0:22:53.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Men of Judah,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.62,0:22:58.08,Default,,0,0,0,,each of you is demanding interest from your brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.16,0:23:02.12,Default,,0,0,0,,You should be ashamed of yourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.12,0:23:04.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Should you not walk in the fear of our God
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.67,0:23:07.38,Default,,0,0,0,,so that the nations, our enemies,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.38,0:23:09.67,Default,,0,0,0,,cannot reproach us?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.67,0:23:14.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Let us, please, stop this lending on interest.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.64,0:23:17.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Please restore to them their fields,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.26,0:23:19.39,Default,,0,0,0,,vineyards, olive groves, houses,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.98,0:23:24.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and the interest.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.94,0:23:30.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Nehemiah, I will restore the fields this day at sunset.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.65,0:23:36.65,Default,,0,0,0,,We all will restore these things to our brothers.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.45,0:23:40.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Before Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.16,0:23:43.21,Default,,0,0,0,,do you swear to these promises?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.21,0:23:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,We do!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.79,0:23:47.29,Default,,0,0,0,,May the true God shake out from his house
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.29,0:23:51.67,Default,,0,0,0,,every man who does not carry out this promise.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.67,0:23:53.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Amen!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.26,0:23:59.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Meshullam,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.81,0:24:03.94,Default,,0,0,0,,we must inform Tobiah about this.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.90,0:24:08.49,Default,,0,0,0,,This will be successful.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.48,0:24:10.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah will bless it.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.08,0:24:22.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Raham!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.08,0:24:24.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I bring good news.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.08,0:24:25.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.62,0:24:27.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.13,0:24:29.17,Default,,0,0,0,,We have your rent.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.17,0:24:31.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.17,0:24:33.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Come by anytime and collect it.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.84,0:24:35.59,Default,,0,0,0,,But I thought we—
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.59,0:24:38.26,Default,,0,0,0,,What about Simcha?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.93,0:24:44.93,Default,,0,0,0,,She’ll be staying with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.19,0:24:49.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, how were you able to put it together so quickly?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.27,0:24:51.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah always takes care of those
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.19,0:24:53.19,Default,,0,0,0,,who love and obey him.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.53,0:24:57.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Ever since Nehemiah got here,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.53,0:25:00.07,Default,,0,0,0,,things have been getting better and better.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.97,0:25:16.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Nehemiah thinks we’re still as young
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.97,0:25:18.97,Default,,0,0,0,,as when we came here with Ezra.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.97,0:25:20.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ve worked hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.10,0:25:24.31,Default,,0,0,0,,But now Nehemiah treats us like it all fell out of heaven,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.31,0:25:26.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and we just have to pick it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.31,0:25:28.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I worked hard for what I have, didn’t I?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.94,0:25:30.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, you worked hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.15,0:25:32.07,Default,,0,0,0,,If I give back my fields,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.07,0:25:33.61,Default,,0,0,0,,what am I to eat?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.61,0:25:35.45,Default,,0,0,0,,What am I to drink?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.44,0:25:37.03,Default,,0,0,0,,What’s wrong with lending on interest?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.03,0:25:40.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You borrow, you pay with interest.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.03,0:25:42.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Raham, Jehovah just wants us
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.03,0:25:43.66,Default,,0,0,0,,to treat our brothers fairly, doesn’t he?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.66,0:25:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Haven’t you heard a word I said?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.00,0:25:46.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I treat everyone fairly!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.29,0:25:54.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Then why are you so angry?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.30,0:25:56.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m not angry!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.34,0:26:00.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Why are you talking to me like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.34,0:26:02.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I just feel betrayed.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.22,0:26:05.22,Default,,0,0,0,,By whom?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.22,0:26:07.22,Default,,0,0,0,,By the people I’ve lent money to!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.65,0:26:12.36,Default,,0,0,0,,What can I do about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.36,0:26:15.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Only what a wife is supposed to do!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.07,0:26:17.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Give me a son!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:17.19,0:26:19.19,Default,,0,0,0,,If not a son, then a daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.66,0:26:26.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I cannot give you what Jehovah does not give us.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.08,0:26:27.75,Default,,0,0,0,,One day,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.75,0:26:30.09,Default,,0,0,0,,it will be too late.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.30,0:26:43.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I say we write a letter to the king.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.30,0:26:45.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, let’s see what the boy reports when he returns.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.31,0:26:47.15,Default,,0,0,0,,My lord, Sanballat.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.14,0:26:48.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Now what?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.60,0:26:50.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The wall has no more gaps.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.65,0:26:52.28,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:54.57,0:26:57.66,Default,,0,0,0,,How can they advance so quickly?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.65,0:27:01.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, there’s a letter for Tobiah.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.96,0:27:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Nehemiah is forcing
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.96,0:27:20.55,Default,,0,0,0,,landlords to return their fields to the original owners.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.55,0:27:22.14,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re running out of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.14,0:27:23.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Enough!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.73,0:27:30.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell this to Nehemiah:
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.10,0:27:34.73,Default,,0,0,0,,“Come, and let us set a time
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.73,0:27:38.19,Default,,0,0,0,,to meet together in the Valley Plain of Ono.”
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.32,0:27:41.41,Default,,0,0,0,,They’re trying to lure me away from Jerusalem
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.40,0:27:43.40,Default,,0,0,0,,to do me harm.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.62,0:27:51.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Please, tell your master:
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.62,0:27:53.75,Default,,0,0,0,,“I am engaged in a great work,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.75,0:27:55.54,Default,,0,0,0,,“and I am not able to go down.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.54,0:27:57.13,Default,,0,0,0,,“Why should the work stop
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.13,0:27:58.84,Default,,0,0,0,,while I leave it to come to you?”
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.84,0:28:02.09,Default,,0,0,0,,They sent me the same message several times.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.51,0:28:06.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Each time I gave them the same response.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.10,0:28:17.15,Default,,0,0,0,,My lord, he has rejected your offer a fourth time.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.32,0:28:24.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Geshem,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.32,0:28:27.70,Default,,0,0,0,,it’s time to implement your plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.70,0:28:29.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Tobiah,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:29.58,0:28:31.83,Default,,0,0,0,,write this down:
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.83,0:28:34.25,Default,,0,0,0,,“Among the nations it has been heard,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.25,0:28:37.30,Default,,0,0,0,,“and Geshem is also saying it,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.29,0:28:41.09,Default,,0,0,0,,“that you and the Jews
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.09,0:28:43.43,Default,,0,0,0,,“are scheming to rebel.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.43,0:28:47.56,Default,,0,0,0,,That is why you are building the wall.”
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.07,0:29:06.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:07.66,0:29:10.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Give this to Nehemiah.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.89,0:29:33.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell your master:
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.89,0:29:36.14,Default,,0,0,0,,“None of the things you are saying have taken place.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.27,0:29:40.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You are making them up out of your own imagination.”
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.75,0:30:02.92,Default,,0,0,0,,They’re bluffing.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.92,0:30:05.51,Default,,0,0,0,,They’re trying to frighten us into stopping the work.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.51,0:30:08.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, they know that the king won’t change his decree.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.85,0:30:14.86,Default,,0,0,0,,But believe me, they won’t stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.12,0:30:40.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah, I pray,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.46,0:30:43.17,Default,,0,0,0,,strengthen my hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.34,0:30:48.76,Default,,0,0,0,,What can we do to stop him?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.76,0:30:51.18,Default,,0,0,0,,We don’t have much time.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.18,0:30:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The wall is almost complete.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.60,0:31:00.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Sanballat,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.98,0:31:03.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I think I know a way.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.90,0:31:06.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Shemaiah, you called for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.44,0:31:07.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.95,0:31:09.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Quickly!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.12,0:31:13.37,Default,,0,0,0,,You are in great danger.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.37,0:31:15.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And so am I because I know about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.04,0:31:15.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Talk sense, man!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.79,0:31:17.25,Default,,0,0,0,,What danger?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.25,0:31:19.75,Default,,0,0,0,,They’re coming to kill you—by night!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.75,0:31:23.21,Default,,0,0,0,,We must go into the temple and close the doors.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.21,0:31:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Shemaiah,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.01,0:31:27.26,Default,,0,0,0,,should a man like me run away?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.26,0:31:29.14,Default,,0,0,0,,You don’t understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.13,0:31:32.09,Default,,0,0,0,,What would that do to the spirit of the entire nation?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.10,0:31:34.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s the only safe place.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.10,0:31:36.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides, I’m not a priest.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.35,0:31:38.35,Default,,0,0,0,,If I entered the temple,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.35,0:31:39.98,Default,,0,0,0,,that would be valid reason to kill me.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.98,0:31:42.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I will not go in.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.77,0:31:45.36,Default,,0,0,0,,That decision would be foolish, Nehemiah.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.24,0:31:52.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.62,0:31:56.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Tobiah and Sanballat put you up to this,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.54,0:31:58.67,Default,,0,0,0,,didn’t they, you hypocrite?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.66,0:32:00.62,Default,,0,0,0,,May Jehovah remember them
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.62,0:32:02.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and all of you false prophets
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.21,0:32:03.84,Default,,0,0,0,,who keep trying to frighten me.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.84,0:32:06.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Come, Hanani,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.00,0:32:08.04,Default,,0,0,0,,we have work to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.56,0:32:20.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Argh!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.36,0:32:27.57,Default,,0,0,0,,We just kept working day and night.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:27.57,0:32:29.91,Default,,0,0,0,,But before we knew it,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.90,0:32:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,we were finishing the very last section of the wall.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.63,0:32:50.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah helped us to achieve the impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.72,0:32:58.68,Default,,0,0,0,,We were tired,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.68,0:33:00.77,Default,,0,0,0,,but we discovered something we had lost
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.06,0:33:05.69,Default,,0,0,0,,—joy.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.36,0:33:10.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Nehemiah, the wall is complete!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.65,0:33:12.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah! Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.99,0:33:15.53,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s it.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.53,0:33:17.37,Default,,0,0,0,,In just 52 days.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.58,0:33:26.50,Default,,0,0,0,,My lord, it’s from Shemaiah. 
Dialogue: 0,0:33:40.98,0:33:42.32,Default,,0,0,0,,What does it say?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.57,0:33:55.57,Default,,0,0,0,,The wall is complete.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.57,0:33:59.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Only the doors are left to be put in.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.33,0:34:02.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Sanballat, we must act quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.41,0:34:03.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Sanballat . . .
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.71,0:34:06.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop it, Tobiah.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:06.42,0:34:07.76,Default,,0,0,0,,No, there’s still time.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.75,0:34:09.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Write that letter to the king.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.34,0:34:11.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Tobiah,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.09,0:34:13.22,Default,,0,0,0,,don’t you see?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.22,0:34:16.18,Default,,0,0,0,,God must be helping the Jews.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:19.93,0:34:21.27,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s over.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.56,0:34:24.56,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ll lose all control over them.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.61,0:34:29.82,Default,,0,0,0,,This isn’t over.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.66,0:35:23.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Rebuilding the walls was only the beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:23.75,0:35:26.17,Default,,0,0,0,,We would definitely need God’s help
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.17,0:35:28.67,Default,,0,0,0,,for what was coming next.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.72,0:35:38.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you now eager to see\Nthe conclusion of the drama?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.18,0:35:40.81,Default,,0,0,0,,We will enjoy Part II
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.80,0:35:44.18,Default,,0,0,0,,during the final session of this convention.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.18,0:35:47.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The account of Nehemiah teaches us
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.23,0:35:51.78,Default,,0,0,0,,to trust in Jehovah\Nas we carry out our assigned work.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.77,0:35:55.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Throughout this session\Nand the preceding one,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.78,0:35:59.03,Default,,0,0,0,,we have been focusing\Non the vital work
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.03,0:36:01.87,Default,,0,0,0,,of making disciples.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.87,0:36:04.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you recall the key lessons?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.62,0:36:09.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, what disciple-making work\Ndo we look forward to in the future?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:09.25,0:36:14.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Please pay close attention\Nto Brother Stephen Lett of the Governing Body
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.17,0:36:16.42,Default,,0,0,0,,as he delivers the talk
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.42,0:36:21.59,Default,,0,0,0,,“Making Disciples Now Prepares Us\Nfor New World Disciple-Making.”
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.81,0:36:32.65,Default,,0,0,0,,There are many things in life
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.65,0:36:36.45,Default,,0,0,0,,that prepare a person for greater things.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.44,0:36:38.90,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, elementary school
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.91,0:36:41.25,Default,,0,0,0,,prepares a student for high school.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:41.24,0:36:43.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Running shorter races
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.24,0:36:46.54,Default,,0,0,0,,prepares a person to run a marathon.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.54,0:36:48.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Working as an apprentice
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.92,0:36:53.63,Default,,0,0,0,,prepares a worker to serve as a professional.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.63,0:36:56.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, in this talk, we’re going to discuss
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.84,0:37:01.85,Default,,0,0,0,,how disciple-making now prepares us
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.84,0:37:05.59,Default,,0,0,0,,for the greater disciple-making work
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.60,0:37:07.69,Default,,0,0,0,,in the new world.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:07.68,0:37:09.93,Default,,0,0,0,,But first, let’s briefly discuss
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.94,0:37:14.40,Default,,0,0,0,,how making disciples right now\Nbrings a lot of joy.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:14.40,0:37:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Please turn to Psalm 105.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.28,0:37:19.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, this is the theme scripture
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.70,0:37:21.87,Default,,0,0,0,,for today’s program,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:21.87,0:37:24.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Psalm 105:3:
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.45,0:37:27.37,Default,,0,0,0,,“Boast about his holy name.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.37,0:37:32.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Let the hearts\Nof those seeking Jehovah rejoice.”
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.13,0:37:36.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Notice, we’re encouraged\Nto “boast about [Jehovah’s] holy name.”
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.80,0:37:38.80,Default,,0,0,0,,How do we do this?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.80,0:37:41.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, by preaching, teaching,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.30,0:37:45.80,Default,,0,0,0,,helping others come to know\NJehovah and his purposes.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.81,0:37:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And what is the result of this?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:48.48,0:37:52.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, honesthearted ones respond favorably,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:52.31,0:37:54.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and they begin to seek Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.94,0:37:57.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And how are they affected?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:57.03,0:37:59.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, as the second part of that verse read,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.61,0:38:03.95,Default,,0,0,0,,that their hearts overflow with ‘rejoicing.’
Dialogue: 0,0:38:03.95,0:38:08.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, taking it a little further,\Nhow are we affected
Dialogue: 0,0:38:08.66,0:38:12.37,Default,,0,0,0,,when we’re able to help someone\Nstart seeking Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.37,0:38:15.33,Default,,0,0,0,,and get on that road to everlasting life?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.34,0:38:18.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it makes our hearts rejoice,\Nisn’t that true?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.88,0:38:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And in fact, there are\Nvery few things in life
Dialogue: 0,0:38:22.88,0:38:25.17,Default,,0,0,0,,that can bring more joy
Dialogue: 0,0:38:25.18,0:38:28.39,Default,,0,0,0,,than helping someone start seeking Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:38:28.39,0:38:30.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and get on that narrow road to life.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.56,0:38:31.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, think about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:31.77,0:38:34.77,Default,,0,0,0,,To explain Bible truth to them,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:34.77,0:38:37.23,Default,,0,0,0,,to see their face light up
Dialogue: 0,0:38:37.23,0:38:40.57,Default,,0,0,0,,as little light bulbs\Nstart going off in their mind
Dialogue: 0,0:38:40.57,0:38:42.57,Default,,0,0,0,,as they’re learning these truths,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:42.57,0:38:47.41,Default,,0,0,0,,to see them start making changes\Nin their life to please Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:47.41,0:38:51.96,Default,,0,0,0,,to see them become an unbaptized publisher\Nand come up from that baptismal pool
Dialogue: 0,0:38:51.96,0:38:54.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and maybe later get into the pioneer work
Dialogue: 0,0:38:54.42,0:38:57.34,Default,,0,0,0,,—there’s nothing this world can offer
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.34,0:39:00.05,Default,,0,0,0,,(no accomplishment, no paycheck)
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.05,0:39:02.22,Default,,0,0,0,,that can equal the joy
Dialogue: 0,0:39:02.22,0:39:06.39,Default,,0,0,0,,of helping someone start seeking Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:06.39,0:39:10.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Appropriately,\Nthroughout this second day
Dialogue: 0,0:39:10.14,0:39:12.18,Default,,0,0,0,,of our program,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.18,0:39:14.68,Default,,0,0,0,,We have been taught many ways
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.69,0:39:17.94,Default,,0,0,0,,we can improve in our disciple-making skills,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.94,0:39:20.36,Default,,0,0,0,,because it is vital that we do so
Dialogue: 0,0:39:20.36,0:39:25.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and because eternal lives\Nhang in the balance.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.07,0:39:29.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And what is the value of one eternal life?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.87,0:39:33.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, one brother said,\N“If all of Jehovah’s Witnesses pioneered
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.33,0:39:36.58,Default,,0,0,0,,“until the end came and one person
Dialogue: 0,0:39:36.58,0:39:39.67,Default,,0,0,0,,learned the truth, it would be worth it.”
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.67,0:39:41.71,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s the value of one life.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:41.71,0:39:45.76,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, with all the money, the gold,\Nthe silver, and the diamonds combined,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.76,0:39:48.26,Default,,0,0,0,,you could not buy one eternal life.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.26,0:39:49.89,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s priceless.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.89,0:39:54.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Not one but almost 304,000 thousand
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.06,0:39:58.61,Default,,0,0,0,,were helped to the point of baptism\Nduring the last service year
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.61,0:40:01.20,Default,,0,0,0,,as a result of Jehovah blessing
Dialogue: 0,0:40:01.19,0:40:04.65,Default,,0,0,0,,the disciple-making skills of his people.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.65,0:40:07.11,Default,,0,0,0,,But as we mentioned before,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:07.12,0:40:10.42,Default,,0,0,0,,learning disciple-making skills now
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.41,0:40:14.46,Default,,0,0,0,,prepares us for the even greater
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.46,0:40:18.09,Default,,0,0,0,,disciple-making work of the new world.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.08,0:40:22.63,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, let’s talk\Nabout how vast this work will be
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.63,0:40:26.84,Default,,0,0,0,,—this educational work in the new world.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.84,0:40:31.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Think about it, millions\Nhave been made disciples
Dialogue: 0,0:40:31.85,0:40:35.02,Default,,0,0,0,,during these last years of the last days.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.02,0:40:39.02,Default,,0,0,0,,But in the new world, apparently,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:39.02,0:40:42.73,Default,,0,0,0,,billions of disciples will need to be made.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:42.73,0:40:45.90,Default,,0,0,0,,How much greater is a billion than a million?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:45.90,0:40:48.61,Default,,0,0,0,,One thousand times greater!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.62,0:40:50.91,Default,,0,0,0,,So we’re talking about thousands of times
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.91,0:40:55.67,Default,,0,0,0,,more disciples\Nneeded to be made then than now.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:55.66,0:40:59.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And likely, we will carry on\Nthis work of disciple-making
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.71,0:41:04.30,Default,,0,0,0,,in the new world for centuries,\Nnot just decades,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:04.30,0:41:07.14,Default,,0,0,0,,as is the case in the last days.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:07.13,0:41:10.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And that is really something\Nto think about, isn’t it?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:10.18,0:41:12.81,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, it makes us think of what Jesus said
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.81,0:41:16.81,Default,,0,0,0,,to his disciples at John 14:12.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:16.81,0:41:21.61,Default,,0,0,0,,He told them,\N‘You will do works greater than I am doing.’
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.61,0:41:23.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So, really, we could say that
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.90,0:41:27.57,Default,,0,0,0,,that disciple-making work\Nof the new world will be greater.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:27.57,0:41:32.53,Default,,0,0,0,,More people will be witnessed to\Nand will be made disciples
Dialogue: 0,0:41:32.53,0:41:36.45,Default,,0,0,0,,—a larger area, a longer period of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:36.46,0:41:40.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And undoubtedly,\Ndisciple-making in the new world
Dialogue: 0,0:41:40.58,0:41:45.38,Default,,0,0,0,,will be even more joyful\Nthan disciple-making now.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.38,0:41:49.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, we said before, it’s\Nan indescribable joy to make a disciple now.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:49.55,0:41:52.14,Default,,0,0,0,,But why will it be even more enjoyable?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.14,0:41:54.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, think about the environment.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:54.68,0:41:57.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Satan the Devil will be gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:57.39,0:42:01.35,Default,,0,0,0,,That’ll be like a 100-pound block\Noff of all our shoulders.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.36,0:42:04.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The spirit of the world will no longer exist
Dialogue: 0,0:42:04.32,0:42:06.82,Default,,0,0,0,,—that spirit of the world exhaled by Satan—
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.82,0:42:10.32,Default,,0,0,0,,because Satan will be locked in the abyss;
Dialogue: 0,0:42:10.32,0:42:12.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and, you could say, it’ll be airtight.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:12.57,0:42:16.12,Default,,0,0,0,,He’ll not be able to exhale\Nthe spirit of the world from there.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.12,0:42:19.67,Default,,0,0,0,,One government will rule the entire earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:19.67,0:42:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,All human governments will be gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.88,0:42:26.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And think of this, never again\N—never, ever—
Dialogue: 0,0:42:26.67,0:42:30.59,Default,,0,0,0,,will the unrighteous outnumber the righteous.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:30.59,0:42:33.34,Default,,0,0,0,,They will always be the minority.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:33.35,0:42:35.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So this wonderful environment
Dialogue: 0,0:42:35.93,0:42:39.10,Default,,0,0,0,,will undoubtedly make disciple-making
Dialogue: 0,0:42:39.10,0:42:42.69,Default,,0,0,0,,even more exhilarating in the new world.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.69,0:42:44.78,Default,,0,0,0,,But now let’s think for a moment
Dialogue: 0,0:42:44.77,0:42:49.32,Default,,0,0,0,,about how voluminous the work itself will be.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:49.32,0:42:54.33,Default,,0,0,0,,John 5:28, 29 says that “all those
Dialogue: 0,0:42:54.33,0:42:57.75,Default,,0,0,0,,“in the memorial tombs
Dialogue: 0,0:42:57.75,0:43:00.80,Default,,0,0,0,,will hear [Jesus’] voice and come out”
Dialogue: 0,0:43:00.79,0:43:02.83,Default,,0,0,0,,—{\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}all{\r} in the tombs.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:02.83,0:43:05.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Who will be included among these ones
Dialogue: 0,0:43:05.50,0:43:08.42,Default,,0,0,0,,that will come out of “the memorial tombs”?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:08.42,0:43:11.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, open up to Acts chapter 24,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:11.63,0:43:14.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and let’s notice who will be included
Dialogue: 0,0:43:14.85,0:43:19.35,Default,,0,0,0,,—Acts 24:15:
Dialogue: 0,0:43:19.35,0:43:22.65,Default,,0,0,0,,“And I have hope toward God,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:22.65,0:43:26.95,Default,,0,0,0,,“which hope these men also look forward to,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.94,0:43:31.57,Default,,0,0,0,,“that there is going to be a resurrection
Dialogue: 0,0:43:31.57,0:43:36.33,Default,,0,0,0,,of both the righteous and the unrighteous.”
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.33,0:43:38.54,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you notice, it’s guaranteed.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:38.54,0:43:42.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It is going to happen\N—not maybe or a good possibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.25,0:43:43.63,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s going to happen!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:43.63,0:43:45.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And it’s going to include
Dialogue: 0,0:43:45.63,0:43:48.88,Default,,0,0,0,,“the righteous and the unrighteous.”
Dialogue: 0,0:43:48.88,0:43:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,But now here’s a question:
Dialogue: 0,0:43:50.88,0:43:54.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Why will the righteous\Nwho are resurrected
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.43,0:43:57.02,Default,,0,0,0,,need further education?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:57.01,0:44:00.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, even though\Nthey’re already servants of God,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:00.35,0:44:03.19,Default,,0,0,0,,they will need to learn details
Dialogue: 0,0:44:03.19,0:44:06.57,Default,,0,0,0,,concerning fulfilled prophecies,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:06.56,0:44:09.69,Default,,0,0,0,,the outworking of God’s purposes,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:09.69,0:44:12.61,Default,,0,0,0,,things that have happened since they died.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:12.61,0:44:15.95,Default,,0,0,0,,They’ll need to be\Nbrought up to speed, so to speak.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:15.95,0:44:18.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And how much they’ll need to be taught
Dialogue: 0,0:44:18.70,0:44:23.71,Default,,0,0,0,,will depend largely upon\Nhow long ago they died.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:23.71,0:44:28.72,Default,,0,0,0,,They will also need help\Nto continue in their righteous course
Dialogue: 0,0:44:28.71,0:44:32.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and to obey the things\Nwritten in the scrolls.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:32.84,0:44:37.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Revelation 20:12 talks\Nabout these new scrolls.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:37.30,0:44:40.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It says: “I saw the dead,\Nthe great and the small,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:40.97,0:44:45.98,Default,,0,0,0,,“standing before the throne,\Nand scrolls were opened. . . .
Dialogue: 0,0:44:45.98,0:44:49.19,Default,,0,0,0,,“The dead were judged\Nout of those things written
Dialogue: 0,0:44:49.19,0:44:52.65,Default,,0,0,0,,in the scrolls according to their deeds.”
Dialogue: 0,0:44:52.65,0:44:55.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And {\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}The Watchtower{\r} said this\Nabout those new scrolls.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:55.57,0:44:59.78,Default,,0,0,0,,It said: “These scrolls\Nwill most likely set forth
Dialogue: 0,0:44:59.79,0:45:04.42,Default,,0,0,0,,“Jehovah’s requirements\Nfor mankind at that time.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:04.41,0:45:09.08,Default,,0,0,0,,“By studying these, all people,\Nincluding resurrected ones,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:09.09,0:45:12.59,Default,,0,0,0,,“will be able to know God’s will for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:12.59,0:45:15.55,Default,,0,0,0,,“These scrolls will surely give us
Dialogue: 0,0:45:15.55,0:45:19.76,Default,,0,0,0,,further insight into Jehovah’s mind.”
Dialogue: 0,0:45:19.76,0:45:23.60,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s exciting, indeed, to ponder, isn’t it?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:23.60,0:45:27.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Included among the righteous\Nto be resurrected
Dialogue: 0,0:45:27.77,0:45:30.32,Default,,0,0,0,,will be faithful ones
Dialogue: 0,0:45:30.32,0:45:34.57,Default,,0,0,0,,who will be brought back\Nto serve as “princes.”
Dialogue: 0,0:45:34.57,0:45:38.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Psalm 45:16 says that Jesus
Dialogue: 0,0:45:38.49,0:45:42.83,Default,,0,0,0,,will appoint “princes in all the earth.”
Dialogue: 0,0:45:42.83,0:45:46.83,Default,,0,0,0,,And {\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}The Watchtower{\r} pointed out\Nthat one example would be Daniel.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:46.83,0:45:51.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you remember what Jehovah\Npromised him shortly before he died?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:51.05,0:45:55.89,Default,,0,0,0,,He said, “You will rest,\Nbut you will stand up
Dialogue: 0,0:45:55.88,0:45:59.47,Default,,0,0,0,,for your lot at the end of the days.”
Dialogue: 0,0:45:59.47,0:46:03.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, he’s rested\Nin the grave for some 2,500 years,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:03.47,0:46:06.18,Default,,0,0,0,,but he will “stand up” in the resurrection.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:06.19,0:46:09.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And he’ll take his position\Nas one of these princes,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:09.86,0:46:12.11,Default,,0,0,0,,as pointed out in {\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}The Watchtower.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:12.11,0:46:15.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, of course, Daniel and others like him
Dialogue: 0,0:46:15.57,0:46:18.07,Default,,0,0,0,,will need to be brought up to speed
Dialogue: 0,0:46:18.07,0:46:21.32,Default,,0,0,0,,—updated, trained for their assignments.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:21.33,0:46:24.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, many of the princes will be selected
Dialogue: 0,0:46:24.58,0:46:29.59,Default,,0,0,0,,from the faithful elders\Nwho are taking the lead today,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:29.58,0:46:31.87,Default,,0,0,0,,as pointed out by {\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}The Watchtower.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:31.88,0:46:36.13,Default,,0,0,0,,But, of course, Jesus, the Messianic King,\Nwill make the appointments.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:36.13,0:46:38.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what do we know?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:38.13,0:46:40.17,Default,,0,0,0,,They will be good appointments.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:40.18,0:46:44.02,Default,,0,0,0,,They will be princes\Nwho will truly love the people
Dialogue: 0,0:46:44.02,0:46:48.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and faithfully carry out all the directions
Dialogue: 0,0:46:48.14,0:46:50.31,Default,,0,0,0,,of the heavenly government.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:50.31,0:46:54.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Also included among “the righteous”\Nto be resurrected
Dialogue: 0,0:46:54.73,0:46:57.23,Default,,0,0,0,,will be many of our loved ones
Dialogue: 0,0:46:57.24,0:47:00.95,Default,,0,0,0,,who may have thought they would live\Nto see the end of this system,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:00.95,0:47:03.62,Default,,0,0,0,,but they died in the last days.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:03.62,0:47:07.67,Default,,0,0,0,,But now, what a joy it will be\Nfor you brothers and sisters
Dialogue: 0,0:47:07.66,0:47:11.58,Default,,0,0,0,,to welcome these ones back and teach them
Dialogue: 0,0:47:11.58,0:47:15.71,Default,,0,0,0,,about all the things\Nthat have happened since they died!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:15.71,0:47:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,They’ll need to be brought up-to-date
Dialogue: 0,0:47:18.01,0:47:21.60,Default,,0,0,0,,so they can help\Nin this great disciple-making work.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:21.59,0:47:24.30,Default,,0,0,0,,An example: I think of my mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:24.31,0:47:28.52,Default,,0,0,0,,She was baptized in 1938.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:28.52,0:47:32.77,Default,,0,0,0,,She died in 2012,\Na little over eight years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:32.77,0:47:36.19,Default,,0,0,0,,She really wanted to see\Nthe end of this system.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:36.19,0:47:40.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And she was\Nof that “Judge Rutherford generation.”
Dialogue: 0,0:47:40.07,0:47:43.07,Default,,0,0,0,,She really wanted to see\Nthat “prostitute” destroyed,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:43.07,0:47:46.32,Default,,0,0,0,,but cancer prevented that from happening.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:46.33,0:47:48.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And I remember\Nshortly before she died, I said:
Dialogue: 0,0:47:48.62,0:47:52.67,Default,,0,0,0,,“Mom, I know you wanted\Nto go into the new world
Dialogue: 0,0:47:52.67,0:47:57.63,Default,,0,0,0,,“on the overland passageway\N(never die at all).
Dialogue: 0,0:47:57.63,0:48:00.84,Default,,0,0,0,,“But you’re going to have\Nto take the underground tunnel.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:00.84,0:48:02.84,Default,,0,0,0,,“But the main thing is to get there.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:02.84,0:48:05.30,Default,,0,0,0,,“And you’re going to\Nvery shortly close your eyes,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:05.31,0:48:06.90,Default,,0,0,0,,“and the next thing you’re going to see,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:06.89,0:48:10.23,Default,,0,0,0,,you’re going to open your eyes\Nin that new world.”
Dialogue: 0,0:48:10.23,0:48:12.48,Default,,0,0,0,,But when she comes back,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:12.48,0:48:16.99,Default,,0,0,0,,just think of the things that have happened\Nin the eight years that she’s been gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:16.98,0:48:19.65,Default,,0,0,0,,She’ll have to be\Nbrought up to speed, won’t she?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:19.65,0:48:24.16,Default,,0,0,0,,“This is JW Broadcasting®
Dialogue: 0,0:48:24.16,0:48:28.91,Default,,0,0,0,,from the World Headquarters\Nof Jehovah’s Witnesses.”
Dialogue: 0,0:48:28.91,0:48:31.58,Default,,0,0,0,,She doesn’t even know about the broadcast!
Dialogue: 0,0:48:31.58,0:48:35.08,Default,,0,0,0,,She’ll have to be brought up to speed,\Nbut she’ll be so happy
Dialogue: 0,0:48:35.09,0:48:39.18,Default,,0,0,0,,to learn about this and other developments.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:39.17,0:48:41.26,Default,,0,0,0,,But now here’s a question:
Dialogue: 0,0:48:41.26,0:48:45.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Where will the billions\Nof new disciples come from?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:45.68,0:48:49.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Even though the resurrected righteous ones
Dialogue: 0,0:48:49.35,0:48:51.89,Default,,0,0,0,,will need to be educated,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:51.89,0:48:54.52,Default,,0,0,0,,they’re already disciples, aren’t they?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:54.52,0:48:57.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So where will the new disciples come from?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:57.32,0:49:00.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, ones born after Armageddon
Dialogue: 0,0:49:00.82,0:49:03.32,Default,,0,0,0,,will need to be made disciples.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:03.32,0:49:06.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, there will be a vast multitude
Dialogue: 0,0:49:06.66,0:49:11.04,Default,,0,0,0,,of unrighteous ones\Nwho will return from the Grave.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:11.04,0:49:14.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, they’ll come\Nfrom all different backgrounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:14.63,0:49:19.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And they’ll come back,\Nand they’ll need to be taught.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:19.01,0:49:23.14,Default,,0,0,0,,They’ll need help to accept Christ’s ransom,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:23.13,0:49:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,to obey the things\Nthat are written in the new scrolls,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:26.89,0:49:28.89,Default,,0,0,0,,because most of them will know nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:28.89,0:49:31.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, maybe some studied a while,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:31.52,0:49:34.52,Default,,0,0,0,,but death prevented them from continuing.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:34.52,0:49:39.32,Default,,0,0,0,,But most will know nothing\N—completely unaware about the good news.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:39.32,0:49:44.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And as we said, they’ll come\Nfrom all time periods, locations, cultures.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:44.03,0:49:47.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Some may have been rulers, maybe slaves,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:47.53,0:49:51.37,Default,,0,0,0,,maybe criminals,\Nmaybe self-righteous persons,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:51.37,0:49:53.92,Default,,0,0,0,,maybe ones who died in combat,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:53.92,0:49:56.13,Default,,0,0,0,,died in childbirth,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:56.13,0:49:59.80,Default,,0,0,0,,died of disease\N(perhaps the coronavirus),
Dialogue: 0,0:49:59.80,0:50:03.89,Default,,0,0,0,,died by starvation, natural disaster.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:03.88,0:50:08.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And it seems that the last thought\Non their mind when they died
Dialogue: 0,0:50:08.81,0:50:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,will be the first thought\Nwhen they come back.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:11.43,0:50:13.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I was thinking about the men who threw
Dialogue: 0,0:50:13.94,0:50:16.23,Default,,0,0,0,,the three Hebrews into the fiery furnace,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:16.23,0:50:18.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and they died because of the heat.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:18.82,0:50:23.83,Default,,0,0,0,,They’ll come back\Nwith a vivid memory of that situation,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:23.82,0:50:28.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and yet they’ll have to be taught\Nwhat happened after they died
Dialogue: 0,0:50:28.74,0:50:33.37,Default,,0,0,0,,—how those three Hebrews\Ncame out unharmed.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:33.37,0:50:38.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Just imagine all these backgrounds\Nof ones coming back.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:38.38,0:50:41.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Imagine situations that could develop.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:41.09,0:50:43.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Here is just an example.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:43.13,0:50:45.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Imagine a former ruler
Dialogue: 0,0:50:45.72,0:50:49.22,Default,,0,0,0,,who had hundreds,\Nmaybe thousands, of slaves
Dialogue: 0,0:50:49.22,0:50:51.81,Default,,0,0,0,,who catered to his every desire.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:51.81,0:50:53.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, he comes back in the resurrection,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:53.93,0:50:58.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and his overseer is one of his former slaves.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:58.15,0:51:03.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And he tells him, gives him direction\N(loving direction, but direction)
Dialogue: 0,0:51:03.07,0:51:06.49,Default,,0,0,0,,to plant a tree in a certain location.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:06.49,0:51:08.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, will he humble himself?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:08.66,0:51:11.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Interesting, interesting possibilities.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:11.70,0:51:14.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Think of the atheists\Nwho will be resurrected.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:14.37,0:51:18.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Here they ate Jehovah’s food,\Nthey drank his water,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:18.63,0:51:21.43,Default,,0,0,0,,they breathed his air,\Nthey walked on his ground,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:21.42,0:51:24.26,Default,,0,0,0,,they never gave him any credit,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:24.26,0:51:26.39,Default,,0,0,0,,they never acknowledged him at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:26.38,0:51:30.43,Default,,0,0,0,,It makes us think of the illustration\Nof the pig under the apple tree.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:30.43,0:51:33.60,Default,,0,0,0,,He gobbles up the apples off the ground,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:33.60,0:51:36.73,Default,,0,0,0,,but he never looks up to see\Nwhere they came from.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:36.73,0:51:38.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, we may not use that illustration
Dialogue: 0,0:51:38.98,0:51:42.03,Default,,0,0,0,,with these atheists that come back,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:42.02,0:51:47.03,Default,,0,0,0,,but they will have to be helped to see\Nwhat a selfish life they lived.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:47.03,0:51:50.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And now they’re\Ngoing to have to praise Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:50.07,0:51:54.62,Default,,0,0,0,,acknowledge him, give him honor,\Nglory, and worship.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:54.62,0:51:56.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Will they do so?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:56.62,0:51:58.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it will be up to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:58.50,0:52:02.38,Default,,0,0,0,,But you brothers and sisters\Nwill help such ones.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:02.38,0:52:06.26,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, let’s just ponder
Dialogue: 0,0:52:06.26,0:52:09.81,Default,,0,0,0,,some of these ones that will come back\Nby means of some artwork.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:09.80,0:52:12.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, look at the following artwork, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:12.64,0:52:15.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And it’s going to show you people
Dialogue: 0,0:52:15.56,0:52:18.35,Default,,0,0,0,,from different time periods,\Ndifferent backgrounds,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:18.35,0:52:22.81,Default,,0,0,0,,being taught after they’re resurrected.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:22.82,0:52:25.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And as the artwork displays,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:25.11,0:52:28.24,Default,,0,0,0,,try to imagine yourself teaching ones
Dialogue: 0,0:52:28.24,0:52:30.58,Default,,0,0,0,,of these various backgrounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:09.63,0:54:12.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And brothers and sisters, that artwork
Dialogue: 0,0:54:12.47,0:54:15.85,Default,,0,0,0,,is just a little, tiny sampling
Dialogue: 0,0:54:15.85,0:54:19.15,Default,,0,0,0,,of ones from various\Ntime periods and backgrounds
Dialogue: 0,0:54:19.14,0:54:22.60,Default,,0,0,0,,who will return to the land of the living.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:22.60,0:54:24.64,Default,,0,0,0,,But, as we mentioned,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:24.65,0:54:27.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah will empower Jesus
Dialogue: 0,0:54:27.52,0:54:30.98,Default,,0,0,0,,to resurrect all of these ones
Dialogue: 0,0:54:30.99,0:54:34.45,Default,,0,0,0,,(bringing them back from the memorial tombs)
Dialogue: 0,0:54:34.45,0:54:38.16,Default,,0,0,0,,that will ‘hear his voice,\Nand they will come out.’
Dialogue: 0,0:54:38.16,0:54:41.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And we know it’ll be\Nin a controlled, orderly way.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:41.50,0:54:46.17,Default,,0,0,0,,See, Jehovah “is a God\Nnot of disorder but of peace.”
Dialogue: 0,0:54:46.17,0:54:49.01,Default,,0,0,0,,—1 Corinthians 14:33.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:49.00,0:54:54.01,Default,,0,0,0,,He also wants things\Nto “take place decently and by arrangement.”
Dialogue: 0,0:54:54.01,0:54:56.76,Default,,0,0,0,,—1 Corinthians 14:40.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:56.76,0:54:59.18,Default,,0,0,0,,So if they all came back at once,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:59.18,0:55:03.52,Default,,0,0,0,,that would be\Na chaotic population explosion, wouldn’t it?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:03.52,0:55:06.31,Default,,0,0,0,,They couldn’t even be taught properly.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:06.31,0:55:08.35,Default,,0,0,0,,They couldn’t be cared for.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:08.36,0:55:12.66,Default,,0,0,0,,We know it will be progressive\Nduring the thousand years.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:12.65,0:55:14.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And {\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}The Watchtower{\r} said this:
Dialogue: 0,0:55:14.70,0:55:19.37,Default,,0,0,0,,“Faithful Christians who died\Nshortly before the end of Satan’s system
Dialogue: 0,0:55:19.37,0:55:23.50,Default,,0,0,0,,“will likely be among the first ones raised.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:23.50,0:55:27.71,Default,,0,0,0,,“We can also expect an early resurrection
Dialogue: 0,0:55:27.71,0:55:32.72,Default,,0,0,0,,for the faithful men of old\Nwho will serve as ‘princes.’”
Dialogue: 0,0:55:32.72,0:55:35.76,Default,,0,0,0,,We touched on that previously.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:35.76,0:55:40.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, resurrected ones\Nwill have much to learn,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:40.56,0:55:43.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and you dear brothers and sisters
Dialogue: 0,0:55:43.64,0:55:46.52,Default,,0,0,0,,will have the privilege to help them.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:46.52,0:55:49.36,Default,,0,0,0,,They’ll need to learn\Nabout Jehovah, his qualities,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:49.36,0:55:52.07,Default,,0,0,0,,all the wonderful things he’s done.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:52.07,0:55:56.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Many will need\Nto reject false religious ideas
Dialogue: 0,0:55:56.41,0:55:59.41,Default,,0,0,0,,that they believed in Satan’s world.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:59.41,0:56:01.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Here’s just an example:
Dialogue: 0,0:56:01.45,0:56:04.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Imagine one who really believed
Dialogue: 0,0:56:04.37,0:56:07.37,Default,,0,0,0,,that all good people go to heaven.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:07.38,0:56:11.59,Default,,0,0,0,,But now he’s resurrected,\Nand he’s brought back here to the earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:11.59,0:56:14.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Obviously, he’ll know\Nthat teaching was wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:14.47,0:56:17.89,Default,,0,0,0,,But what about other false teachings\Nthat he believed?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:17.89,0:56:20.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Will he change his mind and heart?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:20.26,0:56:22.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Will he accept these truths?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:22.72,0:56:24.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It’ll be up to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:24.73,0:56:28.11,Default,,0,0,0,,But you brothers and sisters\Nwill help such ones.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:28.10,0:56:30.98,Default,,0,0,0,,There’ll be many others\Nwho will come back
Dialogue: 0,0:56:30.98,0:56:34.53,Default,,0,0,0,,who will have to abandon\Ntheir former way of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:34.53,0:56:38.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I was thinking, as an example, a homosexual.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:38.53,0:56:41.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, this former homosexual\Ncomes back in the resurrection,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:41.78,0:56:43.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and he really thought
Dialogue: 0,0:56:43.79,0:56:46.79,Default,,0,0,0,,—and he was taught, and he came to believe—
Dialogue: 0,0:56:46.79,0:56:50.79,Default,,0,0,0,,that God accepted him with that lifestyle.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:50.79,0:56:54.71,Default,,0,0,0,,But now he’s going to learn\Nabout Jehovah’s moral standards.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:54.71,0:56:56.71,Default,,0,0,0,,He’s going to learn
Dialogue: 0,0:56:56.72,0:57:00.35,Default,,0,0,0,,that Jehovah will not lower his standard\Nto accommodate us.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:00.35,0:57:03.35,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to come up to Jehovah’s standard.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:03.35,0:57:06.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Will he change?\NWill he adjust?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:06.23,0:57:08.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It’ll be up to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:08.23,0:57:11.48,Default,,0,0,0,,But you brothers and sisters\Nwill help such ones
Dialogue: 0,0:57:11.48,0:57:14.15,Default,,0,0,0,,to enjoy life eternal.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:14.15,0:57:19.16,Default,,0,0,0,,All must learn to walk\Nin Jehovah’s righteous ways
Dialogue: 0,0:57:19.16,0:57:22.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and willingly choose to do so.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:22.49,0:57:26.87,Default,,0,0,0,,But now, what if someone\Nrefuses to make the necessary changes?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:26.87,0:57:29.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, {\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}The Watchtower{\r} commented on that.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:29.04,0:57:32.17,Default,,0,0,0,,It said: “After being given ample time,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:32.17,0:57:36.88,Default,,0,0,0,,“maybe even ‘a hundred years,’ to seek God,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:36.88,0:57:41.38,Default,,0,0,0,,“some will show that they refuse\Nto practice righteousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:41.39,0:57:45.81,Default,,0,0,0,,“Justly they will lose life\Nin that new world,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:45.81,0:57:50.82,Default,,0,0,0,,as we can see from Isaiah 65:20,” which says:
Dialogue: 0,0:57:50.81,0:57:54.27,Default,,0,0,0,,“And the sinner will be cursed,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:54.27,0:57:58.61,Default,,0,0,0,,even though he is a hundred years of age.”
Dialogue: 0,0:57:58.61,0:58:01.99,Default,,0,0,0,,But we expect this will be the minority,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:01.99,0:58:05.29,Default,,0,0,0,,that the majority will be delighted\Nto make the adjustments
Dialogue: 0,0:58:05.29,0:58:09.29,Default,,0,0,0,,so that they can live\Nin that wonderful new world.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:09.29,0:58:11.96,Default,,0,0,0,,But I think about what one brother told me
Dialogue: 0,0:58:11.96,0:58:14.34,Default,,0,0,0,,concerning his Bible student.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:14.34,0:58:17.93,Default,,0,0,0,,His Bible student kept saying:\N“Well, how do I know
Dialogue: 0,0:58:17.92,0:58:20.92,Default,,0,0,0,,“I’m going to like life in the new world?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:20.93,0:58:23.14,Default,,0,0,0,,How do I know I’m not going to be bored?”
Dialogue: 0,0:58:23.14,0:58:25.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, finally, the brother told him, he said,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:25.64,0:58:27.85,Default,,0,0,0,,“Well, one thing about it:
Dialogue: 0,0:58:27.85,0:58:32.52,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don’t like being there,\Nyou don’t have to stay.”
Dialogue: 0,0:58:32.52,0:58:35.86,Default,,0,0,0,,That was kind of humorous,\Nbut it’s a lot of truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:35.86,0:58:40.87,Default,,0,0,0,,A person has to willingly want to be there\Nand make the necessary changes.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:40.86,0:58:44.32,Default,,0,0,0,,But we believe the vast majority
Dialogue: 0,0:58:44.33,0:58:47.25,Default,,0,0,0,,will be delighted to do so.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:47.24,0:58:49.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And what a privilege it will be
Dialogue: 0,0:58:49.75,0:58:53.09,Default,,0,0,0,,to teach ones\Nin that new world at a time
Dialogue: 0,0:58:53.08,0:58:57.25,Default,,0,0,0,,when Isaiah 11:9\Nwill be true, which says:
Dialogue: 0,0:58:57.25,0:59:01.34,Default,,0,0,0,,“The earth will certainly be filled\Nwith the knowledge of Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:59:01.34,0:59:05.26,Default,,0,0,0,,as the waters [are] cover[ing] the sea.”
Dialogue: 0,0:59:05.26,0:59:06.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, think about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:06.93,0:59:11.94,Default,,0,0,0,,This earth—71 percent\Nof its surface is covered with water.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:11.94,0:59:15.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you smooth all the land out,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:15.11,0:59:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,sea water would cover planet Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:59:18.23,0:59:21.40,Default,,0,0,0,,one and two thirds miles deep.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:21.40,0:59:23.99,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a watery planet, isn’t it?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:23.99,0:59:28.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that illustration there in Isaiah\Njust shows how prolific
Dialogue: 0,0:59:28.70,0:59:31.70,Default,,0,0,0,,—how widespread, how filled—\Nthe earth will be
Dialogue: 0,0:59:31.71,0:59:34.80,Default,,0,0,0,,“with the knowledge of Jehovah” at that time.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:34.79,0:59:39.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And that wonderful knowledge\Nwill enable faithful humans
Dialogue: 0,0:59:39.51,0:59:44.52,Default,,0,0,0,,to grow to perfection\Nand to sufficiently be equipped
Dialogue: 0,0:59:44.51,0:59:49.47,Default,,0,0,0,,to face and pass the final test
Dialogue: 0,0:59:49.47,0:59:52.31,Default,,0,0,0,,at the end of the thousand years.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:52.31,0:59:55.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And the good things\Nthat you dear brothers and sisters
Dialogue: 0,0:59:55.19,0:59:58.19,Default,,0,0,0,,have learned today\Nin the second day of our program
Dialogue: 0,0:59:58.19,1:00:01.94,Default,,0,0,0,,—what you’ve learned today\Nabout helping your Bible students now—
Dialogue: 0,1:00:01.95,1:00:04.49,Default,,0,0,0,,will help you in the new world.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:04.49,1:00:07.33,Default,,0,0,0,,As you learned, you learned how to teach
Dialogue: 0,1:00:07.33,1:00:10.67,Default,,0,0,0,,your Bible students\Nto feed themselves spiritually,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:10.66,1:00:15.33,Default,,0,0,0,,to attend the meetings,\Nto avoid bad associations,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:15.33,1:00:18.58,Default,,0,0,0,,to overcome unclean habits,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:18.59,1:00:22.64,Default,,0,0,0,,to develop a personal relationship\Nwith Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:22.63,1:00:27.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Those very same things\Nyou will need to teach these new ones
Dialogue: 0,1:00:27.26,1:00:30.43,Default,,0,0,0,,that come back in the resurrection.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:30.43,1:00:35.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So, at this time, let’s review\Nsome of the good things
Dialogue: 0,1:00:35.10,1:00:38.40,Default,,0,0,0,,that we have learned today\Nabout disciple-making.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:38.40,1:00:43.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And let’s meditate on how these skills\Nwill help in the new world.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:43.32,1:00:46.11,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, look at this video, please
Dialogue: 0,1:00:46.11,1:00:49.99,Default,,0,0,0,,—a brief video that gives us some highlights
Dialogue: 0,1:00:49.99,1:00:52.62,Default,,0,0,0,,from our first symposium,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:52.62,1:00:56.67,Default,,0,0,0,,which was entitled “Improve Your Skills.”
Dialogue: 0,1:01:00.67,1:01:04.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Since there’s no death or pain in heaven,\Nwhere would this promise apply?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:05.51,1:01:07.14,Default,,0,0,0,,The earth.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:07.14,1:01:09.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you like to learn\Nhow to be part of that future?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:10.76,1:01:14.01,Default,,0,0,0,,If these are God’s promises,\Nwouldn’t it make sense to go to his Word
Dialogue: 0,1:01:14.02,1:01:15.69,Default,,0,0,0,,to find out how to enjoy them?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:15.69,1:01:17.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe we can think of it this way.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:17.06,1:01:21.65,Default,,0,0,0,,When parents with a severe genetic defect\Nhave children, what happens?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:21.65,1:01:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I get it!
Dialogue: 0,1:01:23.44,1:01:24.82,Default,,0,0,0,,No study is perfect.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:24.82,1:01:28.07,Default,,0,0,0,,She’s making some effort; focus on that.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:28.07,1:01:32.28,Default,,0,0,0,,If anyone’s enthusiasm\Nis contagious, it’s yours.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:33.75,1:01:36.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I can help, if you want.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:36.25,1:01:39.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The real question is, Do you trust him?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:39.46,1:01:43.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to; I really do.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:46.93,1:01:50.73,Default,,0,0,0,,As we saw in that video,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:50.72,1:01:54.22,Default,,0,0,0,,we want to improve our skills.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:54.22,1:01:57.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And in the symposium, we saw six areas
Dialogue: 0,1:01:57.98,1:02:00.15,Default,,0,0,0,,in which we can improve our skills.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:00.15,1:02:02.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And each one of the six videos
Dialogue: 0,1:02:02.15,1:02:05.11,Default,,0,0,0,,in that symposium\Ndiscussed one of those skills.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:05.11,1:02:10.12,Default,,0,0,0,,In review, Neeta, in the first video\N(the Bible study conductor),
Dialogue: 0,1:02:10.12,1:02:15.13,Default,,0,0,0,,used questions to help the interested person
Dialogue: 0,1:02:15.12,1:02:18.58,Default,,0,0,0,,see the practical value of the Bible.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:18.58,1:02:21.96,Default,,0,0,0,,In the second video, the next time they met,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:21.96,1:02:26.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Neeta unleashed the power of God’s Word
Dialogue: 0,1:02:26.01,1:02:29.26,Default,,0,0,0,,by showing her student scriptures
Dialogue: 0,1:02:29.26,1:02:32.51,Default,,0,0,0,,that highlight our spiritual need.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:32.51,1:02:34.64,Default,,0,0,0,,In the third video,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:34.64,1:02:38.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Neeta illustrated Adamic sin
Dialogue: 0,1:02:38.48,1:02:42.74,Default,,0,0,0,,by likening it to inherited illness.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:42.73,1:02:44.73,Default,,0,0,0,,In the fourth video,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:44.73,1:02:46.94,Default,,0,0,0,,when her Bible student\Nseemed to be losing interest,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:46.94,1:02:49.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Neeta learned the importance
Dialogue: 0,1:02:49.32,1:02:52.99,Default,,0,0,0,,of enthusiasm to motivate.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:52.99,1:02:57.37,Default,,0,0,0,,In the fifth video,\NNeeta showed empathy
Dialogue: 0,1:02:57.37,1:03:00.54,Default,,0,0,0,,for her student’s stressful circumstances
Dialogue: 0,1:03:00.54,1:03:03.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and provided practical help.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:03.04,1:03:06.29,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, in the last (the sixth) video,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:06.30,1:03:10.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Neeta’s conviction and Scriptural reasoning
Dialogue: 0,1:03:10.30,1:03:14.35,Default,,0,0,0,,helped to reach her student’s heart
Dialogue: 0,1:03:14.35,1:03:17.81,Default,,0,0,0,,so that she reconsidered her situation
Dialogue: 0,1:03:17.81,1:03:20.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and her views on morals.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:20.98,1:03:25.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you just imagine how you’ll use\Nthose six skills in the new world?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:25.61,1:03:27.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Think about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:27.40,1:03:29.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You’ll use questions, won’t you?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:29.40,1:03:31.99,Default,,0,0,0,,You’ll use questions to help resurrected ones
Dialogue: 0,1:03:31.99,1:03:35.99,Default,,0,0,0,,see the practical value\Nof the Bible and the new scrolls.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:35.99,1:03:39.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And, by the way,\Nthe Bible will be used in the new world.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:39.58,1:03:43.54,Default,,0,0,0,,You will unleash the power of God’s Word
Dialogue: 0,1:03:43.54,1:03:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and the power of the scrolls\Nby showing these new ones scriptures.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:48.01,1:03:52.31,Default,,0,0,0,,You will use good illustrations\Nto help them reason.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:52.30,1:03:56.35,Default,,0,0,0,,You will use enthusiasm to motivate.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:56.35,1:03:58.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You will show empathy,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:58.56,1:04:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,especially for ones who have scars
Dialogue: 0,1:04:02.40,1:04:06.82,Default,,0,0,0,,as a result of a horrible life\Nin Satan’s old world.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:06.82,1:04:09.91,Default,,0,0,0,,You will also use conviction
Dialogue: 0,1:04:09.90,1:04:14.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and Scriptural reasoning\Nto reach their heart.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:14.91,1:04:18.50,Default,,0,0,0,,But now let’s move to our second symposium,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:18.50,1:04:22.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and it was entitled “Accept Jehovah’s Help.”
Dialogue: 0,1:04:22.04,1:04:25.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And we discussed three aids\Nthat Jehovah gives us.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:25.25,1:04:30.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s look at this brief video\Nthat will remind us of that second symposium.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:32.18,1:04:36.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Her real issue was getting to know\Nsomeone that she can’t see.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:36.47,1:04:38.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe that’s the best place to begin.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:38.47,1:04:42.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I did some research, \Nand I think you’ll really like what I found.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:42.39,1:04:44.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Come, come, sit down.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:46.11,1:04:48.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ve tried everything\Nto get Jade to a meeting.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:48.98,1:04:51.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you tried bringing\Nother people on the study?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:52.53,1:04:53.74,Default,,0,0,0,,You were in a band?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:53.74,1:04:54.91,Default,,0,0,0,,“So sweet.”
Dialogue: 0,1:04:54.91,1:04:55.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, I love that song!
Dialogue: 0,1:04:55.91,1:04:57.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I actually have that vinyl.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:57.49,1:05:00.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Look, I know you’re busy.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:00.29,1:05:01.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You have no clue, do you?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:01.75,1:05:03.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ve got to go.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:04.75,1:05:06.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So I asked him to help Jade
Dialogue: 0,1:05:06.92,1:05:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and then left it with him.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:13.47,1:05:16.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, as reminded in that video,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:16.22,1:05:19.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah provides research tools,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:19.39,1:05:22.23,Default,,0,0,0,,he provides the brotherhood,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:22.23,1:05:26.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and he provides help by means of prayer.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:26.02,1:05:29.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And you’ll use those things\Nin the new world, obviously.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:29.69,1:05:33.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Just like Neeta, she used research tools
Dialogue: 0,1:05:33.11,1:05:37.61,Default,,0,0,0,,to prepare to discuss evolution\Nwith her student.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:37.62,1:05:40.17,Default,,0,0,0,,When she realized\Nshe had a limited understanding
Dialogue: 0,1:05:40.16,1:05:42.29,Default,,0,0,0,,of the student’s background,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:42.29,1:05:44.71,Default,,0,0,0,,she sought help from the brotherhood.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:44.71,1:05:46.71,Default,,0,0,0,,She brought along a publisher
Dialogue: 0,1:05:46.71,1:05:50.21,Default,,0,0,0,,who had a similar background to her student.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:50.21,1:05:54.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And in that third video,\Nwhen her student resisted
Dialogue: 0,1:05:54.34,1:05:58.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Neeta’s encouragement\Nto prepare for her Bible study,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:58.10,1:06:01.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Neeta prayed to Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,1:06:01.27,1:06:04.61,Default,,0,0,0,,to help her and to motivate the student.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:04.60,1:06:07.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And we know Jehovah hears prayers.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:07.48,1:06:10.07,Default,,0,0,0,,But imagine:\NYou’ll use research tools,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:10.07,1:06:12.24,Default,,0,0,0,,you’ll use the brotherhood,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:12.24,1:06:16.29,Default,,0,0,0,,you’ll use prayer\Nto make disciples in the new world.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:16.28,1:06:19.53,Default,,0,0,0,,But now let’s go to that third symposium:
Dialogue: 0,1:06:19.53,1:06:22.95,Default,,0,0,0,,“Help Your Bible Students to . . .”
Dialogue: 0,1:06:22.95,1:06:26.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And we talked about five things\Nwe want to help them to do.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:26.54,1:06:28.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s look at this video,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:28.75,1:06:32.50,Default,,0,0,0,,which will remind us of that third symposium.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:34.05,1:06:36.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Which do you remember more from our studies,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:36.43,1:06:40.23,Default,,0,0,0,,the answers or the things\Nthat touch your heart?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:40.22,1:06:41.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:41.68,1:06:45.43,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s asking how Jehovah feels about something
Dialogue: 0,1:06:45.44,1:06:47.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and then asking what that means for me.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:47.52,1:06:50.23,Default,,0,0,0,,My meeting part tonight covers that point.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:50.23,1:06:51.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Why don’t you come?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:52.40,1:06:54.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m having some people over this weekend.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:54.94,1:06:59.49,Default,,0,0,0,,It wasn’t the club, but it was still fun.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:59.49,1:07:02.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Beating it felt impossible.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:02.41,1:07:06.04,Default,,0,0,0,,“Be made new\Nin your dominant mental attitude.”
Dialogue: 0,1:07:06.04,1:07:09.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I remembered one of the Psalms:\N“I will walk in your truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:09.08,1:07:12.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Unify my heart to fear your name.”
Dialogue: 0,1:07:16.42,1:07:20.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, as reminded, there are five things
Dialogue: 0,1:07:20.01,1:07:22.72,Default,,0,0,0,,we want to help our students to accomplish.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:22.72,1:07:27.60,Default,,0,0,0,,In that first video in the symposium,\NNeeta helped her student learn
Dialogue: 0,1:07:27.60,1:07:32.40,Default,,0,0,0,,to feed herself spiritually by demonstrating
Dialogue: 0,1:07:32.40,1:07:35.57,Default,,0,0,0,,how she herself prepared for their study.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:35.57,1:07:37.57,Default,,0,0,0,,In the second video,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:37.57,1:07:40.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Neeta returned to the subject\Nof meeting attendance
Dialogue: 0,1:07:40.45,1:07:43.33,Default,,0,0,0,,by pointing out that the next meeting
Dialogue: 0,1:07:43.33,1:07:47.71,Default,,0,0,0,,would consider a question\Nshe had raised previously.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:47.71,1:07:50.13,Default,,0,0,0,,In the third video,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:50.13,1:07:54.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Neeta helped her student\Nto seek good association
Dialogue: 0,1:07:54.38,1:07:58.47,Default,,0,0,0,,by arranging for her\Nto attend a Christian gathering.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:58.47,1:08:00.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Then in the fourth video,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:00.89,1:08:04.77,Default,,0,0,0,,when it became clear that the student\Nwas not ready to be a publisher
Dialogue: 0,1:08:04.77,1:08:07.40,Default,,0,0,0,,because of an unclean practice,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:07.39,1:08:12.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Neeta gently helped her\Nto appreciate what it means
Dialogue: 0,1:08:12.40,1:08:17.41,Default,,0,0,0,,to become and remain clean in Jehovah’s eyes.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:17.40,1:08:20.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And then in the last video, that fifth one
Dialogue: 0,1:08:20.66,1:08:22.66,Default,,0,0,0,,—most important—
Dialogue: 0,1:08:22.66,1:08:24.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Neeta helped her student
Dialogue: 0,1:08:24.79,1:08:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to develop strong love for Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,1:08:28.00,1:08:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that would be so strong
Dialogue: 0,1:08:30.00,1:08:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that she would be able\Nto resist pressure from the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:34.00,1:08:38.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you can imagine\Nthat you’ll use the very same skills.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:38.47,1:08:41.39,Default,,0,0,0,,You’ll try to help your students there
Dialogue: 0,1:08:41.39,1:08:44.60,Default,,0,0,0,,to accomplish the same\Nfive things we discussed.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:44.60,1:08:47.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You’ll help them to learn\Nto feed themselves spiritually.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:47.56,1:08:50.35,Default,,0,0,0,,You’ll help them to attend meetings.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:50.35,1:08:53.90,Default,,0,0,0,,You’ll help them to see the need\Nto seek out good association,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:53.90,1:08:57.07,Default,,0,0,0,,to avoid unclean practices
Dialogue: 0,1:08:57.07,1:08:59.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and, most important,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:59.65,1:09:03.53,Default,,0,0,0,,to develop deep love for Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:03.53,1:09:05.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, it’s obvious
Dialogue: 0,1:09:05.66,1:09:10.12,Default,,0,0,0,,that our skills, our experience,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:10.12,1:09:14.42,Default,,0,0,0,,our qualities learned now\Nin the disciple-making work
Dialogue: 0,1:09:14.42,1:09:18.09,Default,,0,0,0,,will be very valuable in the new world.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:18.09,1:09:21.93,Default,,0,0,0,,You’ll be able to put these skills\Nto good use then.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:21.93,1:09:26.81,Default,,0,0,0,,So let’s all strive to improve as teachers.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:26.81,1:09:29.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And that’s what Titus 1:9 says,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:29.43,1:09:33.89,Default,,0,0,0,,that we should\N“[hold] firmly to the faithful word
Dialogue: 0,1:09:33.90,1:09:37.45,Default,,0,0,0,,as respects [our] art of teaching.”
Dialogue: 0,1:09:37.44,1:09:40.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And we want to be artists\N—the “art of teaching.”
Dialogue: 0,1:09:40.82,1:09:43.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You may have heard\Nthe difference between a laborer,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:43.57,1:09:46.03,Default,,0,0,0,,a craftsman, and an artist.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:46.03,1:09:50.87,Default,,0,0,0,,A laborer uses his back;\Na craftsman has to add his mind;
Dialogue: 0,1:09:50.87,1:09:54.04,Default,,0,0,0,,but an artist adds his heart.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:54.04,1:09:57.71,Default,,0,0,0,,We don’t want to be\Njust laborers or craftsmen, but artists
Dialogue: 0,1:09:57.71,1:10:01.46,Default,,0,0,0,,—really putting our heart\Ninto the disciple-making work.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:01.47,1:10:03.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And it does take effort.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:03.47,1:10:07.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s look at one last scripture\Nhere in 1 Timothy chapter 4
Dialogue: 0,1:10:07.31,1:10:10.90,Default,,0,0,0,,—the effort involved—\Nand it’s worth the effort.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:10.89,1:10:14.02,Default,,0,0,0,,First Timothy 4:15:
Dialogue: 0,1:10:14.02,1:10:19.03,Default,,0,0,0,,“Ponder over these things;\Nbe absorbed in them,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:19.03,1:10:21.45,Default,,0,0,0,,“so that your advancement
Dialogue: 0,1:10:21.44,1:10:24.44,Default,,0,0,0,,“may be plainly seen by all people.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:24.45,1:10:28.50,Default,,0,0,0,,“Pay constant attention\Nto yourself and to your teaching.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:28.49,1:10:33.37,Default,,0,0,0,,“Persevere in these things, for by doing this
Dialogue: 0,1:10:33.37,1:10:37.96,Default,,0,0,0,,“you will save both yourself\Nand those who listen to you.”
Dialogue: 0,1:10:37.96,1:10:42.51,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s true now;\Nit will be true in the new world.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:42.51,1:10:45.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And Jehovah is providing what we need
Dialogue: 0,1:10:45.34,1:10:50.14,Default,,0,0,0,,—he’s giving us excellent training;\Nhe provides excellent tools.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:50.14,1:10:54.23,Default,,0,0,0,,We want to make good use\Nof both of these provisions.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:54.23,1:10:56.65,Default,,0,0,0,,But we do want to give this caution:
Dialogue: 0,1:10:56.65,1:10:58.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Don’t be overwhelmed, please.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:58.65,1:11:00.65,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ve discussed a lot of skills,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:00.65,1:11:03.61,Default,,0,0,0,,a lot of suggestions,\Nbut don’t be overwhelmed.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:03.61,1:11:05.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah is going to help you.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:05.70,1:11:08.20,Default,,0,0,0,,He will bless your efforts to do your best.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:08.20,1:11:10.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And we encourage you to just pick out
Dialogue: 0,1:11:10.49,1:11:14.08,Default,,0,0,0,,one or two skills at first and work on those.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:14.08,1:11:17.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And then you can move on to other things.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:17.17,1:11:20.47,Default,,0,0,0,,In conclusion, think about this:
Dialogue: 0,1:11:20.46,1:11:24.59,Default,,0,0,0,,There are many secular skills practiced today
Dialogue: 0,1:11:24.59,1:11:28.34,Default,,0,0,0,,that will not even exist in the new world.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:28.35,1:11:33.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Doctors (no doctors), nurses, optometrists,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:33.23,1:11:37.32,Default,,0,0,0,,undertakers, locksmiths, lawyers
Dialogue: 0,1:11:37.31,1:11:41.15,Default,,0,0,0,,—such professions will not even exist.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:41.15,1:11:45.32,Default,,0,0,0,,But your skills as a disciple-maker
Dialogue: 0,1:11:45.32,1:11:47.70,Default,,0,0,0,,will be in high demand.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:47.70,1:11:51.95,Default,,0,0,0,,You will be able\Nto use these skills to the full,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:51.95,1:11:56.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and you will definitely rejoice greatly
Dialogue: 0,1:11:56.92,1:12:00.92,Default,,0,0,0,,as you share in this voluminous,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:00.92,1:12:03.05,Default,,0,0,0,,this enormous,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:03.05,1:12:06.30,Default,,0,0,0,,new world educational campaign
Dialogue: 0,1:12:06.30,1:12:09.01,Default,,0,0,0,,soon to come.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:10.01,1:12:12.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Brother Lett,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:12.01,1:12:15.89,Default,,0,0,0,,for that exciting preview\Nof the work that lies ahead of us!
Dialogue: 0,1:12:17.35,1:12:19.35,Default,,0,0,0,,This program has highlighted
Dialogue: 0,1:12:19.36,1:12:23.11,Default,,0,0,0,,the joy we can find in making disciples.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:23.11,1:12:27.11,Default,,0,0,0,,What can we look forward to\Nin the next two sessions?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:27.11,1:12:29.45,Default,,0,0,0,,The scripture theme for those sessions
Dialogue: 0,1:12:29.45,1:12:33.08,Default,,0,0,0,,is taken from Psalm 37:4, which says:
Dialogue: 0,1:12:33.08,1:12:35.79,Default,,0,0,0,,“Find exquisite delight in Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:35.79,1:12:39.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and he will grant you\Nthe desires of your heart.”
Dialogue: 0,1:12:41.67,1:12:44.09,Default,,0,0,0,,The next session begins with a symposium
Dialogue: 0,1:12:44.09,1:12:47.93,Default,,0,0,0,,that will show how we can imitate\Nthe apostle Paul and others
Dialogue: 0,1:12:47.93,1:12:51.73,Default,,0,0,0,,by rejoicing in all circumstances.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:51.72,1:12:54.06,Default,,0,0,0,,In the final session,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:54.06,1:12:57.77,Default,,0,0,0,,we will enjoy the conclusion\Nof the Nehemiah drama,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:57.77,1:13:01.48,Default,,0,0,0,,followed by an uplifting closing talk.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:01.48,1:13:06.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Now let all in attendance stand,\Nif you are able to do so,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:06.49,1:13:10.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and sing together song number 140.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:10.20,1:13:14.54,Default,,0,0,0,,This song invites us\Nto imagine our future joy.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:14.54,1:13:19.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It is entitled “Life Without End—At Last!”
Dialogue: 0,1:13:19.54,1:13:24.55,Default,,0,0,0,,After the song, you may have\Nyour local concluding prayer.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:24.55,1:16:11.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Again, that’s song number 140.
